<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-749-781  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 749 781.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Dec 19 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Philly area drops 1-plus calling. (Bell of Pennsylvania)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Blankenhorn, Dana.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Bell Telephone Company of Pennsylvania (Services).andO;Topic:     Telephone companiesCommunications Service SuppliersTelecommunications ServicesPennsylvania.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>PHILLY AREA DROPS 1-PLUS CALLING 12/19/90 PHILADELPHIA, PENNSYLVANIA, U.S.A.,andO;1990 DEC 19 (NB) -- Bell of Pennsylvania customers is dropping the &quot;1-plus&quot;from toll calls in the 215 area code, starting January 14.andP;  The change isbeing made to increase the capacity of the 215 area code to handle newnumbers.andP;  The company claims 1 million new numbers will be available afterthe change becomes final, September 22.andM;&quot;Previously, when you dialed 1 the equipment recognized that as a toll call.andO;By eliminating the 1, you make it available as part of a central office code.andO;So you will now have exchanges like 131 and 158,&quot; spokesman John Caltagironeexplained to Newsbytes.andP;  Problems may occur, he admitted, if people dialingoutside the 215 area code forget their 10-digit numbers after dialing 7digits.andM;Demand for cellular service and fax numbers are driving demand for phonenumbers, the company says, and without the change the company would have runout of numbers in the 215 area code by 1992.andP;  Over the last 6 years over434,000 new access lines have been used.andP;  All Bell of Pennsylvaniaoperator-assisted calls within the 215 area must be dialed by using &quot;0&quot; plus&quot;215&quot; plus seven digits.andP;  Currently such a call is made by dialing &quot;0&quot; plusseven digits.andP;  Anyone with questions about the new dialing procedure shouldcall 800-555-5000.andM;Phone companies throughout the U.S.andP;  are facing the same problem.andP;  The firstsolution was to add exchanges like 805 and 916, using the numbers previouslygiven only to area codes.andP;  The next step, after the access lines being freedup by Bell of Pennsylvania now run out, is to split the area code, as wasdone last year in Boston and Houston.andM;(Dana Blankenhorn/19901218/Press Contact: Bell of Pennsylvania, JohnCaltagirone, 215-466-8768)</TEXT></DOC>